x4freetext: TITANIUM AND NICKEL FOR 15 MEV NEUTRONS-.
THE T(D,N)HE-4 REACTION USING A TRITIATED
ZR TARGET BOMBARDED WITH 200 KEV DEUTERIUM IONS.
.NAURAL METAL DISCS, 15.0 CM IN DIAMETER AND WITH
TIME OF FLIGHT TECHNIQUES WERE EMPLOYED
FOR THE GAMMA RAY SPECTRA BUT NOT FOR THE NEUTRON
SPECTRA BECAUSE OF INSUFFICIENT RESOLUTION AT
HIGH NEUTRON ENERGY. THE PULSE HIGHT DISTRI-
BUTIONS WERE UNFOLDED WITH A COMPUTER CODE.
THE ALPHA PARTICLES FROM THE NEUTRON
PRODUCING REACTION WERE COUNTED WITH A PLASTIC
SCINTILLATOR AND WAS USED TO NORMALIZE THE
A 3 IN. BY 3 IN. NE-213 LIQUID SCINTILLATOR FOR
A 1 MM. DIA. BY 0.1 MM THICK NE-111 PLASTIC
SCINTILLATOR TO DETECT THE ALPHAS FROM THE NEUTRON
.UNFOLDING OF SPECTRA WITH THE COMPUTER CODE FERDO.
.ACCURACY OF NEUTRON DATA IS NOT SO GOOD AND
MORE EXPERIMENTS MAY BE NEEDED TO OBTAIN FINAL
A.P.T. JAPAN CODE CHANGED TO JPN
- GAMMA RAY SELF-SHIELDING IN THE SAMPLE.
ERROR OF SOURCE NEUTRON DECREASING IN SAMPLE,
ERROR BECAUSE OF NOISE IN THE ASSOCIATED
PARTICLE COUNTING IN THE NEUTRON PRODUCING REACTION,
ERROR IN THE EFFECT OF PERIPHERAL MATERIALS OF
.THE ERROR FROM THE UNFOLDING OF THE SPECTRA VARIED
